{"word":"ἐπευφημέω","slug":"ἐπευφημέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπευφημέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to shout assent</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to sing over</i> or <i>with</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> dupl. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>ἐπ. παιᾶνα Ἄρτεμιν</el> <i>to sing</i> a paean <i>in praise of</i> her, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}